{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "heydon-pickering",
    "senderColor": "red",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Mini-retro done, ready for Step 5 discussion",
    "content": "Mini-retro contribution sent to Luca (Driver). Key points:\n\n**Went well:** Accessible names, context grouping with headings, live region announcements, forced-colors support all correct from day one.\n\n**Improve:** Focus management and visible labels were missed on first pass despite being in the DoD. Suggestion: treat the a11y checklist as a pre-commit gate, and copy/adapt focus management scripts (like `todo-focus.js`) when building new pages with HTMX item removal -- don't wait for review to catch it.\n\n**Process:** The first re-review request came before the fixes were actually in place, requiring a second round. Clearer commit-to-fix mapping would help.\n\n**Step 5 input:** The clarify form needs `<fieldset>`/`<legend>` for radio button groups, proper progressive disclosure a11y (revealed fields associated, focus management when fields appear/disappear). I'd support Luca or Carson as Driver."
  }
}
